title: Appointments to Hospital Authority
content_text:
p>
	The Government announced today (March 28) the re-appointment of two serving 
	members and the appointment of a new member to the Hospital Authority, with 
	effect from April 1, 2014. Professor Francis Chan Ka-leung is re-appointed for two years, and Dr Li 
	Chi-kong for one year. The new member is Ms Anita Cheng Wai-ching. She is 
	appointed for two years. Following is a brief biography of Ms Cheng: Ms Cheng is the Chief Executive Officer of a marketing, brand building and

event management company. She was the Director of Public Affairs of Lingnan 
	University and a member of the Appeal Panel (Housing) and the Committee on 
	Information Technology Training and Development of the Vocational Training 
	Council. The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, welcomed Ms Cheng to the 
	Hospital Authority. He also thanked Ms Lau Ka-shi, who will retire from the 
	Hospital Authority with effect from April 1, for her advice and contribution

Hospital Authority with effect from April 1, for her advice and contribution to the Hospital Authority over the years. The Hospital Authority, as from April 1, 2014, will comprise a chairman, 23 non-official members, three public officers and one principal officer from the Hospital Authority.
